### File Structure
```
GymMembership/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── membership_plans.html
│   ├── plan_details.html
│   ├── class_schedule.html
│   ├── trainer_profiles.html
│   ├── trainer_detail.html
│   ├── pt_booking.html
│   ├── workout_records.html
│   └── log_workout.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (trainer photos, icons, etc.)
│
└── data/
    ├── memberships.txt
    ├── classes.txt
    ├── trainers.txt
    ├── bookings.txt
    └── workouts.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles routing, page rendering, reading and writing data from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and implements all business logic for the GymMembership web application. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic is consolidated here for simplicity and maintainability.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web pages, each corresponding to one of the nine pages specified in the requirements. These templates use Python web framework templating (e.g., Flask Jinja2) to dynamically render data.

  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard page with member highlights and navigation buttons.  
  - `membership_plans.html` — Displays membership plans with filtering and navigation.  
  - `plan_details.html` — Shows detailed information about a selected membership plan.  
  - `class_schedule.html` — Displays class schedules with search and filter options.  
  - `trainer_profiles.html` — Lists trainers with search and filter capabilities.  
  - `trainer_detail.html` — Detailed profile page for a specific trainer.  
  - `pt_booking.html` — Personal training booking page with form inputs.  
  - `workout_records.html` — Displays workout history and progress tracking.  
  - `log_workout.html` — Form page to log new workout sessions.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, and images used by the web pages.

  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across the application.  
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).  
  - `images/` — Stores images such as trainer photos and icons.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in local text files as specified, serving as the data persistence layer.

  - `memberships.txt` — Membership plans data.  
  - `classes.txt` — Fitness classes data.  
  - `trainers.txt` — Trainer profiles data.  
  - `bookings.txt` — Personal training session bookings data.  
  - `workouts.txt` — User workout records data.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, frontend templates, static resources, and data storage, aligning well with the project requirements and enabling straightforward development and maintenance.
